CHELICERAE. Fused basally, reddish brown, stridulatory lines laterally. Fangs reddish brown, with thin setae around them (
Fig. 17
).

PALPS. Trochanters, femora and patellae pale brown, tibiae and tarsi reddish brown. Tibiae cylindrical, tarsi conical (
Figs 18–19
).

GENITAL AREA. Seminal receptacles asymmetric, S-shaped (
Fig. 28
). Base of seminal receptacles oval and wide, sclerotized (
Fig. 28
). See variation section for more details (
Figs 36–39
).

